<paragraph blockId="18.[164,779,1102,1583]" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis box="[164,530,1102,1124]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[391,516,1103,1124]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11A–E</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Epandrial complex prominent in resting position, clearly visible in lateral view from the ventrolateral margin of tergite 5 (
<figureCitation box="[172,270,1194,1216]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Epandrium long, convex, and relatively narrow. Hypandrial arms long robust, not bent anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[245,343,1255,1277]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Cerci, in posterior view, wide, relatively short, with brush-like fine medioclinate setulae arising from median slope of a longitudinal carina (
<figureCitation box="[172,313,1347,1369]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11C, D</figureCitation>
), Cerci, in lateral view, not or very slightly bent posteriorly, not widened apically (
<figureCitation box="[172,268,1408,1430]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
); medioventral sclerite not visible in profile (
<figureCitation box="[172,270,1439,1461]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Lateral margin of cerci sinuous without a distinct lobe (
<figureCitation box="[318,415,1470,1492]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Medial preapical tooth of cerci well developed (
<figureCitation box="[380,478,1500,1522]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
). Surstylus very long, paddle-like, strongly bent posteriorly almost down to the base (
<figureCitation box="[280,377,1561,1583]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[164,243,980,999]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetId="figure-327@18.[323,1283,196,950]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Dolichocolon caudatum sp. nov. (holotype). A, posterior end of abdomen in lateral view; B, terminalia in lateral view; C, terminalia in posterior view; D, cerci in posterolateral view; E, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440725/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="562">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
